<subSubSection pageId="485" pageNumber="486" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName genus="Harpalii" lsidName="" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="genus">Harpalii</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1810: Tabula Synoptica. Type genus: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Harpalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 1802. Note. The oldest available name for this taxon is 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Graphipterinae">Graphipterinae</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 1802. I agree with Bouchard et al. (2011: 122) that the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Harpalinae" lsidName="" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Harpalinae">Harpalinae</taxonomicName>
should be maintained.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="485" pageNumber="486" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
Worldwide, with about 19,600 species arrayed here in two supertribes for convenience: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Pterostichitae" lsidName="" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="genus">Pterostichitae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Harpalitae" lsidName="" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="genus">Harpalitae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
